            <!--Note subtypes include bibliographical, biographical, contextual, and geographical.-->
            <div type="note" subtype="bibliographical">
                <head type="title">Drawings from the Tour of 1833</head>
                <p>Drawings that Ruskin made during the <ref type="note" subtype="contextual" target="tour_of_1833_note.php">Tour of 1833</ref>--and possibly, some of them, after the family's return home--are listed here 
                    in topographical order according to the tour itinerary. I am grateful to <persName corresp="#SWILDMAN">Stephen Wildman</persName> for the basis of this list. Several of the 
                    <date when="1833">1833</date> tour sketches can no longer be traced.</p>
                
                <p>Omitted from this list are the drawings that Ruskin made as vignettes to illustrate <ref type="apparatus" target="account_of_a_tour_on_the_continent_apparatus.php">Account of a Tour on the Continent</ref>, 
                    which occupied Ruskin's creative energy for about a year following the family's return in September 1833 (see <ref type="apparatus" target="account_of_a_tour_on_the_continent_apparatus.php#DATE">Date</ref>), 
                    and which are documented as part of ERM's edition of the "Account". The tour sketches are distinct from the vignettes in style and other features, even though Ruskin based some of the vignettes on tour sketches, as explained in 
                    <ref type="apparatus" target="account_of_a_tour_on_the_continent_apparatus.php#COMPOSITEILLUSTRATEDTRAVELOGUEILLUS">Account of a Tour on the Continent: Missing and Unidentified Drawings for the Composite&#x2010;Genre Illustrated Travelogue (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIX">MS IX</title>) and Related <date when="1833">1833</date> Tour Sketches</ref>. 
                    The vignettes are not tour sketches, but imitations of how British readers consumed Continental scenery in context of British print culture of the 1830s. Nonetheless, the list may perpetuate 
                    some confusion in the catalogues of Ruskin's drawings between tour sketches and vignettes for the "Account", since too little is known about some drawings that can no longer be traced. 
                    Some titles listed as tour sketches in the catalogues may in fact have been vignettes intended for use directly in the fair-copy version of the "Account", <title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIX">MS IX</title>, 
                    but which became separated from the manuscript or were never permanently affixed to the manuscript. For bibliographical details, see again 
                    <ref type="apparatus" target="account_of_a_tour_on_the_continent_apparatus.php#COMPOSITEILLUSTRATEDTRAVELOGUEILLUS">Missing and Unidentified Drawings for the Composite&#x2010;Genre Illustrated Travelogue (<title type="manuscript" corresp="#MSIX">MS IX</title>) and Related <date when="1833">1833</date> Tour Sketches</ref>.</p>
                
                <p>In the list below, titles cited with quotation marks refer to captions that <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> wrote directly on the tour sketch. Titles that are not <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s, 
                    or that cannot be definitely traced to him, are cited without quotation marks. Citations of <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#JRWORKSLE"><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE"><hi rend="italic">Works</hi></title></ref> 
                    refer, unless otherwise specified, to the <title type="catalogue" corresp="#CATALOGUEOFRUSKINSDRAWINGSLE">&#x201C;Catalogue of <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName>&#x02BC;s Drawings&#x201D;</title> compiled for the <title type="book" corresp="#JRWORKSLE">Library Edition</title> (38:215&#x2013;306); 
                    citations of <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#WGCLIFEOFJR1893"><persName corresp="#WGC">Collingwood</persName>, <title type="book" corresp="#WGCLIFEOFJR1893"><hi rend="italic">Life and Work of <persName corresp="#JR">John Ruskin</persName></hi></title></ref>, refer to the 
                    <title type="catalogue" corresp="#WGCCATALOGUEOFRUSKINSDRAWINGS">&#x201C;Catalogue of Drawings by <persName corresp="#JR">Mr. Ruskin</persName> (<date notBefore="1829" notAfter="1859">1829&#x2013;1859</date>)&#x201D;</title> (1:238&#x2013;43); and 
                    citations of <ref type="bibliography" target="bibliography.php#WGCRUSKINEXHIBITION1900"><persName corresp="#WGC">Collingwood</persName>, <title type="catalogue" corresp="#WGCRUSKINEXHIBITION1900"><hi rend="italic"><persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> Exhibition</hi></title></ref>, 
                    refer to the catalogue of the <persName corresp="#JR">Ruskin</persName> Exhibition, <placeName corresp="#CONISTON">Coniston</placeName>, <date when="1900">1900</date>.</p>
                <p>
